d_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/iiokws","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/iiokws/netbsd_gsoc_2026_report_testing_compat"},{"short_id":"rkj3j4","created_at":"2026-07-21T17:47:54.327-05:00","title":"Bringing the modern web to the original iPad mini","url":"https://seg6.space/posts/resurrecting-ipad-mini","score":10,"flags":2,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"seg6","user_is_author":true,"tags":["browsers","objectivec","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rkj3j4","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rkj3j4/bringing_modern_web_original_ipad_mini"},{"short_id":"0btjlt","created_at":"2026-07-21T17:38:33.131-05:00","title":"An Engineer’s Guide to USB Type-C","url":"https://www.ti.com/lit/eb/slyy228/slyy228.pdf","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"dgv","user_is_author":false,"tags":["book","hardware","pdf"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/0btjlt","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/0btjlt/engineer_s_guide_usb_type_c"},{"short_id":"ohl1dh","created_at":"2026-07-21T17:36:12.089-05:00","title":"The Value of Domain Knowledge in Software","url":"https://www.gustavwengel.dk/value-of-domain-knowledge","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"stip","user_is_author":false,"tags":["practices"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ohl1dh","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ohl1dh/value_domain_knowledge_software"},{"short_id":"aw3pbi","created_at":"2026-07-21T17:13:28.637-05:00","title":"Hardening Rust Code For Production","url":"https://corrode.dev/blog/hardening-rust/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"vaguelytagged","user_is_author":false,"tags":["rust"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/aw3pbi","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/aw3pbi/hardening_rust_code_for_production"},{"short_id":"lzgtkz","created_at":"2026-07-21T16:59:43.207-05:00","title":"Parallelizing Compilation: In-Process vs Multi-Process","url":"","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":8,"description":"\u003cp\u003eI'm not sure if there are already good names for this, but I can't find anything useful when I look online.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eObviously, when compiling programs, parallelizing the work is crucial. There seem to be two main approaches:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCompiler is single-threaded, build system spawns N compilers (C, C++, others I'm sure)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCompiler is multi-threaded (Rust, Zig)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI'm looking into this because I'm looking at designing a programming language, and I have fast compilation as an explicit goal. Zig and Rust obviously have some of the same ideas but wildly different compilation speeds. C is known to be quite fast to compile, while C++ templates are slow(?).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn terms of parallelization, why is it that a parallel compiler seems to be the choice for newer languages? Is this a coincidence or explicitly required because of e.g. circular imports?\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"I'm not sure if there are already good names for this, but I can't find anything useful when I look online.\r\n\r\nObviously, when compiling programs, parallelizing the work is crucial. There seem to be two main approaches:\r\n- Compiler is single-threaded, build system spawns N compilers (C, C++, others I'm sure)\r\n- Compiler is multi-threaded (Rust, Zig)\r\n\r\nI'm looking into this because I'm looking at designing a programming language, and I have fast compilation as an explicit goal. Zig and Rust obviously have some of the same ideas but wildly different compilation speeds. C is known to be quite fast to compile, while C++ templates are slow(?).\r\n\r\nIn terms of parallelization, why is it that a parallel compiler seems to be the choice for newer languages? Is this a coincidence or explicitly required because of e.g. circular imports?","submitter_user":"Riolku","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","plt"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/lzgtkz","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/lzgtkz/parallelizing_compilation_process_vs"},{"short_id":"jmuobj","created_at":"2026-07-21T15:44:50.262-05:00","title":"Your Agentic Workflow's Cache Keepalive Costs 8x Too Much","url":"https://blog.mempko.com/keeping-the-kv-cache-warm-measuring-prompt-cache-eviction-across-anthropic-openai-and-google/","score":4,"flags":1,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"mempko","user_is_author":true,"tags":["vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/jmuobj","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/jmuobj/your_agentic_workflow_s_cache_keepalive"},{"short_id":"rwdmjn","created_at":"2026-07-21T15:39:54.470-05:00","title":"Free Ink · An open ecosystem for e-readers","url":"https://freeink.org/","score":29,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Yogthos","user_is_author":false,"tags":["hardware"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rwdmjn","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rwdmjn/free_ink_open_ecosystem_for_e_readers"},{"short_id":"7nrek3","created_at":"2026-07-21T15:38:04.837-05:00","title":"OpenAI model breaks out of security sandbox, hacks Hugging Face for data to pass test","url":"https://openai.com/index/hugging-face-model-evaluation-security-incident/","score":26,"flags":5,"comment_count":10,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"dustyweb","user_is_author":false,"tags":["security","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/7nrek3","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/7nrek3/openai_model_breaks_out_security_sandbox"},{"short_id":"nv7xhn","created_at":"2026-07-21T14:57:49.414-05:00","title":"COSMIC DE’s First Seven Months","url":"https://system76.com/blog/post/cosmic-de-first-seven-months","score":15,"flags":0,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"RaphGL","user_i